From Mark Ashley Subject Marian Apparitions The Blessed Virgin Mary appeared to Catherine Laboure a nun of the sisters of Charity on July at Rue du Bac Sister Catherine was awakened late that night by a small boy age or who was literally glowing with some sort of interior The child led her to the sanctuary of the chapel where he promised the Virgin Mary was to be found awaiting Our Lady appeared to her and instructed her for two hours or more on matters pertaining to her life and to the future of France and the On November Our Lady appeared again to She instructed her to have a medal She told her that those who wore this medal would enjoy special protection from the Mother of God and would receive great In less than a year there were three more In June of the medals were a Many reports were received by those who wore Within two years of its issuing the medal was known as the Miraculous Medal Catherine died in Her body to this day is remarkably preserved incorrupt She was canonized on July Her body lies in the chapel at the motherhouse on the Rue du Bac where she had her first meeting with Our The apparition on November was of average height and clothed in white with a veil that flowed over the head and fell to the Above the altar a pyramid painted to represent God's all knowing wisdom looked down on Our Lady's feet rested on a white globe and there was also a green serpent with yellow spots that she was stepping In her hands was a golden ball that represented the Great streams of light issued from her hands and she also showed Catherine an image of two hearts the Sacred Heart wrapped in piercing thorns and her own heart punctured by a The sword represented her suffering with The apparitions announced the onset of the great battle and forewarned that a dark era lay in the immediate It was the apparition leading up to the recent Our Lady began to dispense And with the globe she revealed herself in worldwide dispute with the forces of the She told Catherine The times a